==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Presentive
<hw>Pre*sent"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Philol.)</fld>
<def>Bringing a conception or notion directly before the mind;
presenting an object to the memory of imagination; -- distinguished from
<xex>symbolic</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How greatly the word ⟦ldquo⟧will⟦rdquo⟧ is felt to have lost
<qex>presentive</qex> power in the last three centuries.</q>
<rj><qau>Earle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Pre*sent"ive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pre*sent"ive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presently</ent>⟦br⟧
